Welcome to

For education & homework guidance

Let me introduce myself: my name is Lara James.

I am a certified teaching assistant. My passion is guiding children between the ages of 4 and 12. I am married and the mother of a daughter.

I have been working in education as a teaching assistant for quite some time. Because of this I have given support to many children in primary education. Individually, but also in small groups. Letter Jungle originated from the initials of my name.

Personal attention

During my work I have experienced that personal attention and time for the children leads to the best results.

Children develop optimally when they receive tailor-made education, education that matches their personal situation.

As self-confidence grows, the child's capabilities grow.

Extra time and personal attention are essential for progress in your child's learning process. Something that is becoming increasingly difficult in the range of schools given the size of the classes and the number of children requiring extra care.

Letter Jungle wants to provide children with a quiet, safe place, where they receive much-needed attention and professional support, so that they can move on with the essential basic knowledge and with confidence.
